# Deploying {{SERVICE_NAME}}

This service deploys to GCP Cloud Run via Cloud Build, authenticated from
GitHub Actions through Workload Identity Federation. The bootstrap script
(in the `gcloud-cloud-run-deployment` skill) provisions everything; this
runbook documents day-to-day operations.

## Manual deploy

```bash
./deploy.sh
```

Honors:
- `REGION=us-central1 ./deploy.sh` — override region (default `{{REGION}}`)
- `PREVIEW_TAG=pr-42 ./deploy.sh` — preview revision (no traffic)

## CI/CD

- **`.github/workflows/deploy.yml`** — push to `main` deploys to prod. Manual `workflow_dispatch` also available.
- **`.github/workflows/pr.yml`** — every PR runs `lint` + `type-check`, then deploys a preview revision to a tagged Cloud Run URL (no traffic). Comments the URL back on the PR. Cleanup runs automatically when the PR closes.

## Required GitHub Variables

(Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions → **Variables** tab.)

| Name | Value |
|---|---|
| `GCP_PROJECT_ID` | The GCP project ID |
| `GCP_DEPLOYER_SA` | `gh-actions-deployer@<PROJECT_ID>.iam.gserviceaccount.com` |
| `GCP_WORKLOAD_IDENTITY_PROVIDER` | `projects/<PROJECT_NUMBER>/locations/global/workloadIdentityPools/github-pool/providers/github-provider` |

These are non-sensitive (project IDs, SA emails, WIF provider paths) — that's why they're Variables, not Secrets.

## Custom domain (optional)

```bash
gcloud run domain-mappings create \
  --service={{SERVICE_NAME}} \
  --domain=your-domain.com \
  --region={{REGION}}
```

Follow the DNS records gcloud prints.

