## Rotating / extending

- **Adding a runtime env var:** edit `deploy.sh`, add `--set-env-vars=KEY=VAL` to the `gcloud run deploy` block, redeploy.
- **Adding a runtime secret:**
  ```bash
  echo -n "VALUE" | gcloud secrets create my-secret --data-file=-
  PROJECT_ID=$(gcloud config get-value project)
  PROJECT_NUMBER=$(gcloud projects describe $PROJECT_ID --format='value(projectNumber)')
  gcloud secrets add-iam-policy-binding my-secret \
    --member="serviceAccount:${PROJECT_NUMBER}-compute@developer.gserviceaccount.com" \
    --role="roles/secretmanager.secretAccessor"
  ```
  Then add `--update-secrets=ENV_VAR=my-secret:latest` to `deploy.sh`.
- **Build-time `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` vars:** add `ARG` declarations to the Dockerfile builder stage, add `--build-arg` to `cloudbuild.yaml`, pass via `--substitutions` from `deploy.sh`.
